  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNestled in the scenic western mountains near Madrid, Spain, \u003cstrong\u003eCasamontesa\u003c/strong\u003e, designed by \u003ca href=\"https://www.lucasyhernandezgil.com/#/home\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener external noreferrer\" data-wpel-link=\"external\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eLucas y Hernández-Gil\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e of \u003ca href=\"https://krestadesign.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener external noreferrer\" data-wpel-link=\"external\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eKresta Design\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, stands at the crossroads of nostalgia and modern design. Originally built in the 1970s as part of a hotel complex, the bungalow exhibits an intriguing fusion of rustic charm and mid-century modern aesthetics, wrapped in a touch of kitsch. Despite its quirky elements, the house has retained its character, which became the focal point of a careful redesign.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=558531\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-558531\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/09/Casamontesa-House-Madrid-Kresta-Design-Lucas-y-HernandezGil-2-810x847.jpg\" alt=\"A modern living room with a stone fireplace, gray sofa, and white coffee table. Two white pendant lights hang above a marble countertop in the foreground.\" width=\"810\" height=\"847\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/09/Casamontesa-House-Madrid-Kresta-Design-Lucas-y-HernandezGil-2-810x847.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/09/Casamontesa-House-Madrid-Kresta-Design-Lucas-y-HernandezGil-2-800x837.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/09/Casamontesa-House-Madrid-Kresta-Design-Lucas-y-HernandezGil-2-768x803.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/09/Casamontesa-House-Madrid-Kresta-Design-Lucas-y-HernandezGil-2.jpg 1280w\" si